title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should display in data set dialog.
description: When calling the stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, no data is returned. The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: No data is returned in the query result page when the stored procedure is called from an Oracle database.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR: Steps to reproduce: 1. Call the stored procedure from an Oracle database. 2. Verify that the query result is stored in the output parameter as an object. 3. Go to the query result page and check if any data is displayed. 4. Open the edit data set dialog and ensure that the output parameter is visible.
